I have a whole soapbox/theory about The Tornado and the meaning behind it.
5:38 PM
I was watching a YouTube video of two guys, listening to Coco Moon and reacting to it, and they were listening to the tornado. Right after the screaming part, the music softens, and one of the guys comments, “The storm must be lifting.” But according to the lyrics, the storm doesn’t stop until later in the song; the music indicates peace despite being in a violent storm. It shows that you can have peace even in the midst of a storm. Idk if Adam did that on purpose (he probably did), but I thought that was pure genius!
